name: KT Dawg
description: KT Dawg offers a complex mixture of effects that soothes and uplifts. This hybrid blends anti-inflammatory pain relief and pleasurable physical effects with a focused, cerebral buzz. KT Dawg’s aroma is pungent, reeking of skunk and forest floor. The earthy terpenes mellow on the palate while stimulating appetite and creativity. KT Dawg is a cross of Kunduz,  Tang Tang, and Stardawg.

highlightedReviews.text: Simply amazing. Took away all of my pain in my back and ankles. Felt so relaxed and calm. And felt creative as well!

I picked this particular strain up at Herbal Remedies Dispensary (Quincy, IL).  High percentage, bulk popcorn flower.  I have become a fan of Cresco as of late.  They always throw a Boveda 58 in their bulk flower!  Definite perk!  When I opened this up it looked like a dead octopus still trying to camouflage itself.  Very dark initially, little red/orange hairs everywhere like feelers, and pungent.  Almost looked like a rats nest.  Lightened up as it got a little bit of air it seemed.  Very dark once ground!  It didn't look good really, but it is.  I just did back-to-back, one-hit rips out of my C2 Bell Base and i'm higher than Charlie Sheen!  The tingly, energetic, feel good experience.  Pain relief, heavy eyes (RED), and relaxed.
